n* Chapter 30: {{Nihongo|Autumn Sky|\u3042\u304d\u306e\u305d\u3089|Aki no Sora}}\n* ''Afterwords'' was dedicated to [[Project Itoh|It\u014d Keikaku]]\n| Summary         = Sora's father returns home and soon discovers Sora and Aki's forbidden relationship, taking Aki home with him. As Sora laments his loneliness, Runa allows him to pretend she is Aki whilst she has sex with him. Sora decides to go see Aki, but she refuses to go back with him as their father is dying with an illness, who reveals that he and their mother were siblings. After the father passes away, Aki and Sora say their goodbyes. The two later meet up again at their mother's grave, and the series concludes with an open ending on whether they will come back together or separate for each other's happiness.\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list/footer}}\n\n===OVA===\nThere are two [[original video animation|OVA]] adaptations of ''Aki Sora'', both produced by [[Hoods Entertainment]], with [[Takeo Takahashi]] as director, [[Jukki Hanada]] as scriptwriter and [[Kazuya Kuroda]] as character designer and chief animation director.<ref name=\"ANN OVA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2009-07-11/aki-sora-3rd-manga-volume-to-bundle-anime-dvd |title=''Aki Sora''{{'}}s 3rd Manga Volume to Bundle Anime DVD (Updated 2) |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |date=July 11, 2009 |accessdate=June 10, 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140403034655/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2009-07-11/aki-sora-3rd-manga-volume-to-bundle-anime-dvd |archivedate=April 3, 2014 |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref><ref name=\"ANN OVA2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2010-02-05/new-aki-sora-line-crossing-ova-staff-confirmed|title=New ''Aki Sora'' 'Line-Crossing' OVA, Staff Confirmed|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 5, 2010|accessdate=December 27, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140403061057/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2010-02-05/new-aki-sora-line-crossing-ova-staff-confirmed|archivedate=April 3, 2014}}</ref> The first OVA was released with the third volume of the manga on December 18, 2009.<ref name=\"ANN OVA\" />\n\nA second OVA adaptation, titled {{nihongo|''Aki Sora ~Yume no Naka~''|\u3042\u304d\u305d\u3089~\u5922\u306e\u4e2d~|Aki Sora ~In a Dream~}} was released by [[Pony Canyon]] in two parts and features a different voice cast from the first OVA.<ref name=\"OVA2\" /><ref name=\"OVA3\" /> The first part was released on July 30, 2010 and the second part was released on November 17, 2010.<ref name=\"OVA2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/artist/34386/products/cinema/867552/1/|script-title=ja:\u3042\u304d\u305d\u3089\uff5e\u5922\u306e\u4e2d\uff5e\u3000\u4e0a\u5dfb |trans-title=Aki Sora ~In a Dream~ Part 1|publisher=[[Oricon]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=December 27, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106070308/http://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/artist/34386/products/cinema/867552/1/|archivedate=January 6, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"OVA3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/artist/34386/products/cinema/867553/1/|script-title=ja:\u3042\u304d\u305d\u3089\uff5e\u5922\u306e\u4e2d\uff5e\u3000\u4e0b\u5dfb |trans-title=Aki Sora ~In a Dream~ Part 2|publisher=[[Oricon]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=December 27, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106070249/http://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/artist/34386/products/cinema/867553/1/|archivedate=January 6, 2014}}</ref> Pony Canyon released a [[Blu-ray Disc|Blu-ray]] of both OVAs on September 19, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/artist/34386/products/cinema/1036738/1/|script-title=ja:\u3042\u304d\u305d\u3089\uff5e\u5922\u306e\u4e2d\uff5e\u3000\uff22\uff4c\uff55\uff0d\uff52\uff41\uff59\u6fc3\u7e2e\u7248\u3010\u5b8c\u5168\u521d\u56de\u9650\u5b9a\u751f\u7523\u3011|trans-title=Aki Sora ~In a Dream~ Blu-ray (Concentrated Edition) (Completed Limited Edition) |publisher=[[Oricon]]|language=Japanese |accessdate=December 27, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106070246/http://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/artist/34386/products/cinema/1036738/1/|archivedate=January 6, 2014}}</ref> The ending theme for this OVA is \"Thx!\" by Mai Kotouge. [[Media Blasters]] has licensed the second OVA under its Kitty imprint.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-07-24/media-blasters-licenses-aki-sora/yume-no-naka-anime |title=Media Blasters Licenses Aki Sora: Yume no Naka Anime - News |publisher=Anime News Network |date=November 7, 2012 |accessdate=November 11, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131227150509/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-07-24/media-blasters-licenses-aki-sora/yume-no-naka-anime |archivedate=December 27, 2013 }}</ref>\n\n====Episode list====\n{{Episode table |total_width=98 |overall= |title= |airdate= |overallT=No. |titleT=Episode title |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = \n| AltTitle        = \n| RAltTitle       = -\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2009|12|18}}<ref name=\"JA3\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/4253181767/|title=\u3042\u304d\u305d\u3089\u7b2c3\u5dfb\u4e88\u7d04\u9650\u5b9a\u7248(\u30aa\u30ea\u30b8\u30ca\u30eb\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1DVD\u4ed8) (\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30d4\u30aa\u30f3RED\u30b3\u30df\u30c3\u30af\u30b9) [\u30b3\u30df\u30c3\u30af]|trans-title=''Aki Sora'' Volume 3 Limited Edition (DVD with OVA) (''Champion Red'' Comic) (Comics)|publisher=[[Amazon.com|Amazon.co.jp]]|language=Japanese |accessdate=December 27, 2013}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Sora had become nervous around his older sister Aki, since he had started having lewd thoughts about her. While taking a bath together, Aki masturbates Sora, who runs off in disbelief. The next day, Sora cannot face Aki and runs off, inevitably getting locked in a store room. Aki eventually finds him and the two kiss, later returning home to make love.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| Title           = Aki Sora: In a Dream (Part 1)\n|